EVALUATION USE
--------------

A prospect bank or organization that has been provided this Software by
Timeless Nypo Tech for the purpose of evaluation (a "Pilot") may, for the duration
of the Pilot and solely on its own internal infrastructure:

  (a) install and run the Software,
  (b) ingest and process its own correspondent-banking statements and
      core-banking general-ledger data,
  (c) operate the Software for normal reconciliation activities, and
  (d) make backup copies as required for disaster recovery.

Evaluation use does NOT include any right to:

  (i)   redistribute the Software, in source or compiled form, to any
        third party;
  (ii)  publish, mirror, or open-source the Software or any derivative;
  (iii) sublicense, lease, rent, or sell the Software or access to it;
  (iv)  remove or alter any proprietary notices, copyright statements,
        or branding within the Software;
  (v)   reverse-engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Software except
        to the extent that applicable law expressly permits despite this
        limitation;
  (vi)  use the Software in production beyond the agreed Pilot scope
        without a signed commercial license.

The Pilot terminates automatically (a) at the end of the agreed
evaluation period, (b) upon written notice from Timeless Nypo Tech, or
(c) upon any breach of this License. On termination the Pilot organisation must
remove all copies of the Software from its systems within thirty (30)
days, except where retention is mandated by applicable law (in which
case the Software remains subject to this License for the retention
period).

